            </table>
        </div>

        <h2>Tax Efficiency</h2>
        <p>ETFs are inherently tax-efficient structures, and SCHB is no exception. Its broad market nature means it experiences very low turnover, generating minimal capital gains distributions. For taxable brokerage accounts, SCHB is an excellent long-term hold.</p>

        <div class="faq">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q">What is the SCHB ETF?</div>
                <div class="faq-a">The Schwab US Broad Market ETF (SCHB) is a low-cost exchange-traded fund that tracks the Dow Jones U.S. Broad Stock Market Index, providing exposure to large, mid, and small-cap US equities.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q">What is the expense ratio of SCHB in 2026?</div>
                <div class="faq-a">The expense ratio for SCHB is 0.03%, making it one of the most cost-effective broad market ETFs available to investors, tied with competitors like VTI.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q">How does SCHB compare to VTI?</div>
                <div class="faq-a">SCHB and VTI are very similar, both offering broad US market exposure with identical 0.03% expense ratios. The main difference is the index tracked (Dow Jones for SCHB, CRSP for VTI), resulting in minor holdings variations, but long-term performance is nearly identical.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q">Is SCHB a good investment?</div>
                <div class="faq-a">For investors seeking diversified, low-cost exposure to the entire US stock market, SCHB is an excellent core portfolio holding, particularly for those using Charles Schwab as their broker.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q">Does SCHB pay a dividend?</div>
                <div class="faq-a">Yes, SCHB pays quarterly dividends. The yield fluctuates based on market conditions but generally aligns with the broader US stock market average.</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="methodology">
            <strong>Methodology & Data Sources:</strong>
            <p>Data presented is sourced directly from live market feeds (Yahoo Finance API) as of <span id="current-date"></span>. Expense ratios, AUM, and holdings data reflect the most recent fund disclosures. Returns are calculated based on adjusted close prices to account for dividend reinvestment.</p>
